    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="55"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="from"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> to Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2"
                            type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d55fn1">Sent to the United States Naval Attach, London, via
                        Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-25">25 October
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 396, Personal and secret, from the President for the <gloss
                        target="#t_FormerNavalPerson1">Former Naval Person</gloss>.</p>
                <p>It is a nuisenza to have the influenza. <persName corresp="#p_MRT1"
                        >McIntire</persName> says I need a sea voyage.</p>
                <p>No word from <gloss target="#t_UJ1">U. J.</gloss> yet.</p>
                <p>If he is adamant, what would you think of you and me meeting, with small staffs,
                    in North Africa or even at the Pyramids, and toward the close of our talks get
                    the <gloss target="#t_Generalissimo1">Generalissimo</gloss> to join us for two
                    or three <pb facs="0132" n="40" xml:id="pg_40"/> days? At the same time, we
                    could ask <gloss target="#t_UJ1">U. J.</gloss> to send <persName
                        corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> to the meeting with you and me. Our
                    people propose November 20.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
